commit.message:
Updates for intrusive_ptr refcounting

- Initialize the refcounts with 1
- Use memory orderings that match the implementation of shared_ptr refcounting in libc++/Windows STL
Update build instructions to specify Boost
Replace ArrayVector with Boost static_vector
Switch intrusive pointer implementation to Boost
[cmake] Install generated celestia.cfg

Revert "[qt] Hold the CelestiaCore in a unique_ptr"

This reverts commit db922ab6b8f00d71bb5378bc28c42ba6f9a613ca.
Use pointer
Add TDBToQString
Do not set global locale
Read config from `~/.celestia` path
Add ExtrasDirectories based on configuration
Consistent use of i18n names in GTK/Qt search/goto dialogs
[win] Allow search by path in find dialog
[qt] Hold the CelestiaCore in a unique_ptr
Fix minor issues

Default to "classic" when locale not found

`std::locale()` is `noexcept` returning the "C" locale or the last
locale entered into `std::locale::global(locale)`.

By calling `std::locale::global(std::locale(""))` on start we can
confidently use `std::locale()` to get a locale without crashing.

Move some optional features out of Body class

- Atmospheres
- Ring systems
- Alternate surfaces
- Locations
- Reference marks
- Custom orbit colors
- Custom comet tail colors

Track which features are enabled on a bitfield enum in the Body
class in order to avoid needing to do lookup when the feature isn't
enabled
Remove DSONameDatabase, replace with NameDatabase

Convert Body classification to enum class

Fix bug in cel script orbitflags command - parse correct map.
Fix type mismatch in GTK2 build

Update metainfo files to be better conformant to appdata specs

Signed-off-by: Mattia Verga <mattia.verga@tiscali.it>
Reuse ring render data for all ring systems
Replace shadermanager enums with enum classes
More use of const
Remove some unnecessary usage of Selection
Ensure translation targets are created before RC targets are defined
[qt] Save media to standard paths by default
